                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94116/85: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bucknell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-08-09T19:00:00+01:00"
                            >August 9, 1938—7 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 9—1:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>167. My telegram 93, May 13, 6 p.m. Secretary General has now received a
                    communication from Chinese permanent delegate alleging the use of poison gas by
                    Japanese on Matang front during period July 2 through 5. This communication is
                    accompanied by a medical report supporting Chinese allegations. The note
                    requests that Secretary General transmit communication to members of Council,
                    Assembly and Advisory Committee “for their information and consideration.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bucknell</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
